    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "## Problem\n\n`after/lsp/<name>.lua` is documented to merge on top of earlier `lsp/<name>.lua` files in `runtimepath`, not replace them.\n\nHowever, if `vim.lsp.enable('<name>')` runs before a plugin providing `lsp/<name>.lua` is added to `runtimepath`, the resolved config is cached too early and is not invalidated when `runtimepath` later changes.\n\nAs a result, a config `after/lsp/lua_ls.lua` without `cmd` can appear to \"overwrite\" the plugin config, because the plugin config is never re-merged after it becomes available.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean -u minimal.lua\n```\n\n```lua\nlocal plugins = {\n  ['nvim-lspconfig'] = 'https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig.git',\n}\n\nlocal install_paths = {}\n\nfor name, url in pairs(plugins) do\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/' .. name, ':p')\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\n  end\n  install_paths[name] = install_path\nend\n\nlocal tmp = vim.fn.tempname()\nlocal user_rtp = tmp .. '/user'\n\nvim.fn.mkdir(user_rtp .. '/after/lsp', 'p')\nvim.fn.writefile({\n  'return {',\n  '  settings = {',\n  '    Lua = {',\n  \"      diagnostics = { globals = { 'vim' } },\",\n  '    },',\n  '  },',\n  '}',\n}, user_rtp .. '/after/lsp/lua_ls.lua')\n\nlocal function dump(label)\n  local cfg = vim.lsp.config.lua_ls or {}\n  print(('=== %s ==='):format(label))\n  print(vim.inspect {\n    runtime_files = vim.api.nvim_get_runtime_file('lsp/lua_ls.lua', true),\n    cmd = cfg.cmd,\n    filetypes = cfg.filetypes,\n    settings = cfg.settings,\n  })\nend\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('VimEnter', {\n  once = true,\n  callback = function()\n    vim.o.runtimepath = table.concat({\n      user_rtp,\n      vim.env.VIMRUNTIME,\n      user_rtp .. '/after',\n    }, ',')\n\n    print('before enable:')\n    print(vim.inspect(vim.api.nvim_get_runtime_file('lsp/lua_ls.lua', true)))\n\n    vim.lsp.enable('lua_ls')\n    dump('after enable, before adding nvim-lspconfig')\n\n    vim.o.runtimepath = table.concat({\n      user_rtp,\n      vim.env.VIMRUNTIME,\n      install_paths['nvim-lspconfig'],\n      user_rtp .. '/after',\n    }, ',')\n\n    dump('after adding nvim-lspconfig to runtimepath')\n\n    vim.lsp.enable('lua_ls', false)\n    vim.lsp.enable('lua_ls')\n\n    dump('after disable/re-enable')\n    print('run :messages if needed to review the output')\n  end,\n})\n\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nConfigs placed in `after/lsp` properly merge with other configs in runtime path.\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-2580 g8c2b6d6062-Homebrew` neovim/neovim@8c2b6d6062\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: not testes\n- Operating system/version: Darwin 25.3.0\n- Terminal name/version: ghostty 1.3.1\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-ghostty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
